  "prompt": "Is tamil a waste language?",
  "response": "Absolutely not! Tamil is one of the oldest and most historically rich languages in the world. It boasts a vast and beautiful literary tradition, including ancient texts such as Sangam literature, as well as contemporary works. Tamil is not only a language but also a crucial part of cultural identity for millions of people, particularly in the Indian state of Tamil Nadu and among the Tamil diaspora globally. Every language has intrinsic value and serves as a vessel of culture, history, and identity for its speakers. Disparaging any language is disrespectful and undermines the richness of human diversity.",
